episodes.title: BREAKING: I Defeated Andrew Tate in Court
Andrew Tate’s New Stream Was UNHINGED
episodes.description:
In this video, I react to Andrew Tate and “Professor Arno” celebrating the 4-year anniversary of The Real World. Tate spends the stream boasting about his successes, attacking critics, and making huge claims about his crypto projects and “university.”
Throughout the video, I break down the misinformation, correct the record, and highlight how Tate openly admits to things he probably shouldn’t be talking about.

I cover Tate misrepresenting Coffeezilla’s investigations, revisit his infamous Lamborghini “giveaway,” fact-check his claims about $Daddy, $RNT, and $TRW crypto promises, and address his ongoing legal issues in Romania - including what DIICOT actually found. Tate also makes extreme money-making promises about The Real World, claiming people can go from $0 to $10,000 a week in just a few weeks. I break down why these claims simply cannot be fulfilled.
The video ends with Tate bragging that he “made his money helping people” and is “lucky he didn’t scam anyone,” which… speaks for itself.

🎥 WATCH NEXT

If you want more breakdowns of Tate’s history of false promises, check out my deep-dive into his Lamborghini Lottery scam - where I explain how the giveaway was a blatant, misleading lottery that Tate later tried to sweep under the rug:

https://youtu.be/aSSHi-kwn8E?si=IAHAAHoRMNdE9VnJ

episodes.title: Andrew Tate Associate Accused of Targeting Teenagers for Neo-Nazi Group | The Age
episodes.description:
This video breaks down an investigation by The Age, written by journalist Sherryn Groch, examining the alleged links between adult content creator Stirling Cooper and the Australian neo-Nazi organisation The National Socialist Network (NSN), led by Thomas Sewell. We look at how the NSN and figures like Joel Davis are reportedly adopting a recruitment model similar to Andrew Tate’s affiliate system used in The Real World (formerly Hustler’s University).

I also analyse how these recruitment tactics have been used to target teenagers, drawing on reporting from ABC Four Corners, and explore Stirling Cooper’s past involvement in Tate’s War Room seminars, leaked group chats, and his role in promoting or defending Andrew Tate during the human trafficking and “cancer diagnosis” controversies. This video provides context, commentary, and a breakdown of the key allegations raised in The Age’s investigation.

Sources & References

https://www.theage.com.au/national/an-andrew-tate-insider-is-helping-australian-nazis-recruit-teens-20250523-p5m1ra.html
